    "attributes": {
        "action": "Remove Peru from the Red list and mandatory hotel quarantine",
        "additional_details": "There are many Peruvian expats who have not been able to se ageing family members or any family members as a result of the covid-19 pandemic and being subsequently added to the red list. With work in the office resuming, taking two weeks of quarantine is no longer a viable option for many. Peru has moved quite swiftly with vaccinations and this should be considered as part of the criteria for quarantine. Please consider this.",
        "background": "Please allow fully vaccinated people to travel between the U.K. and Peru without the need to quarantine if they are fully vaccinated.",
